# DRY policy

**Goal:** One authoritative definition per concept. Copy-paste is a bug unless extracted intentionally.

## Single source of truth

| Concern | Authority | Do not duplicate |
|---------|-----------|------------------|
| GROQ | `sanity/lib/queries.ts` | Inline queries in pages/components |
| Data access | `sanity/lib/fetchers.ts` (`get*`) | Direct `safeFetch` in routes |
| CMS types | `lib/types/` | Ad-hoc inline object shapes |
| SEO metadata | `pageMetadata()` in `lib/seo.ts` | Hand-built `<meta>` tags |
| Canonical paths | `lib/paths.ts` | String-concat paths in components |
| Tailwind patterns | `lib/tailwind.ts` (`TW_*`) | Same class string in 2+ files |
| Theme tokens | `tailwind.config.ts` | Raw hex/spacing repeated in TSX |
| Rich text styles | `TW_RICH_TEXT_*` + `.rich-text` in `globals.css` | `prose-*` or per-page typography |
| Site URL / defaults | `lib/seo.ts`, `getSiteSettings()` | Hardcoded domain or phone/email |
| Runtime port | `deploy/runtime.cjs` | Magic `3001` outside deploy docs |
| Contact validation | `lib/contact-schema.ts` | Inline checks in API route |
| Rate limiting | `lib/rate-limit.ts` | Ad-hoc counters in routes |
| Cache tags | `lib/cache-tags.ts` | Untagged fetches |
| Nav tree helpers | `lib/navigation.ts` (`buildNavTree`, `nodeIsActive`) | Logic in `lib/types/` |
| Portable Text wrapper | `components/content/RichTextBody.tsx` | Inline `PortableText` + duplicate `TW_RICH_TEXT_*` |
| Org name fallback | `DEFAULT_SITE_NAME` in `lib/seo.ts` | Hardcoded `'Dar Ul Quran'` in schemas/layout |
| Urdu allowlist | `CLAUDE.md` § Urdu | Parallel English-copy rules elsewhere |

## When to extract

| Signal | Action |
|--------|--------|
| Same class string **2+** times | Add `TW_*` to `lib/tailwind.ts` |
| Same GROQ field set **2+** queries | Private `SCREAMING_SNAKE` fragment in `queries.ts` |
| Same JSX block **2+** routes | Shared component in `components/content/` or `ui/` |
| Same fallback chain **2+** callers | `resolve*` helper in `lib/` |
| Same breadcrumb/path logic | Use `lib/paths.ts` helpers |

## When duplication is OK

- Route-specific composition in thin `page.tsx` files (different section order)
- One-off marketing copy in a single page
- Schema components that share shape but differ in JSON-LD type (`ArticleSchema` vs `CourseSchema`)
- `// urdu-ok` suppressed strings — not a pattern to centralize

## Abstraction limits (avoid over-DRY)

- No generic `<Wrapper>` or `<Container>` unless 3+ real use cases exist
- No premature `lib/utils.ts` — keep helpers next to their domain file
- No shared component props that require 8+ optional flags — split components instead
- Do not merge unrelated fetchers; one `get*` per query concern

## Refactor order (when deduplicating)

1. Identify authority file from table above
2. Move definition there; replace call sites
3. Delete dead code and unused exports
4. `npm run lint && npm run check:urdu` (+ `build` if wide refactor)

